node.text:
Now that summer is over, it’s the perfect time to set new routines. 🌟

Total Body Guide, my exclusive fitness and nutrition program, is now OPEN for enrollment!! 🥳🥳 And this time… we’re getting FIT FOR FALL!! 🍁🌞🍂

Get ready for 21 days of workouts, healthy fall- inspired meals, community, accountability coaching and weekly check-ins with ME, your Coach!! 💝

I take ALL the guesswork out of what and when to eat, how to workout and how to create small goals that drive MAJOR MOMENTUM.⚡️ 

Plus, with my Fit for Fall Bundle, I’ll send you weekly motivational videos for support and mindset strategies to identify and overcome self-limiting beliefs that could be holding you back from having the CONFIDENCE and BODY you want. 🌠

Drop a 🎃 in the comments below and TAG your workout buddy if you’re ready to get Fit for Fall! 🍁🌞🍂👇

How do you sign up?? Head to the Link in my bio!!! 😘 #tbgstrong 

🔥 🎃 🔥 🎃 🔥 🎃 🔥 🎃 🔥 🎃

node.text:
Do you find yourself reminiscing about moments in life before they’re actually over?

I found myself talking about Summer in a past tense last week as if it was already “over” 😱And yet, here we are still in the middle of August with plenty of time to enjoy all the flavors and fun summer has to offer 🍹

👉🏼I promised myself at the beginning of quarantine that I would take some time to enjoy the little things, and not rush through life so much as I used to do👈🏼

Don’t get me wrong, we need things to look forward to, goals to achieve ⭐️, and dreams to work toward. But, we also need to take time and enjoy the present moment 🧘‍♂️

I’m asking you right now, what is one goal you still want to achieve before summer comes to a close? You still have time to change your eating habits, read that book, go run that 5k, or spend more time with family 🏖🌻🏃🏼‍♀️💕

🍒🍉Join me, and download my 28-Day at home workout and meal plan to really make the most of these last few weeks of summer! I can help you achieve those summer goals, and have fun while doing it! 🍑🍍

☀️ Summer isn’t over yet ☀️

Download Stronger Summer today.

💥 Link in Bio.

#tbgstrongersummer #summerisntoveryet #getstrong #tbgstrong #workoutplan #mealplan #enjoylife

node.text:
Groceries can be EXPENSIVE! And I found that most the time I was throwing away food or buying ingredients I already had! And not to mention, every time I opened my fridge I felt overwhelmed with WHAT I COULD make for a healthy meal... So, I decided to take charge and organize my fridge and freezer so that I could support my health goals, reduce stress (an organized room is an organized mind!) and save time and money on my groceries!

Check out this video to see how I organize my fridge and freezer and make healthy simple.

Also, don’t forget to give a *double tap*❤️ to support your girl and lemme know in the comments below if you found this helpful!!👇👇
#getfitwithkrystal #healthymadesimple

node.text:
I’m excited to announce my exclusive TBG LIVE group coaching experience is taking things to the NEXT LEVEL!!🔥 On February 3rd, I’m kicking off a BRAND NEW 4-week Nutrition & Lifestyle course, Reset & Rebalance!!!
🍎🥒🍊🥑🍋🥒🥬 Get ready to be immersed in a whole new world of possibilities where you’ll have your eyes opened to healthy habits, healthy meals, and learn how to become a BOSS in the kitchen. 💥

I’ve partnered with @gardenoflife for 2020 to help spread the word that we are ALL capable of living extraordinary lives- and we make that one choice at a time! ⭐️ 📣Here’s the breakdown: 🍎There will be a daily meal schedule for all 28 days so you know exactly what to eat and drink. 🍋We’ll focus on 25 healthy and simple meals to support your energy, healthy, and vitality so you can look good in your body while feeling great as well! 💻During these four weeks I’ll be holding live classes that educate you on nutrition and lifestyle. This includes a progressive 3-phase meal plan that supports cleansing and weight loss WITHOUT being super-restrictive or complicated. 🎁Don’t worry about workouts because everyone who signs up before January 30th gets a FREE bonus of my top 13 all-time favorite TBG workouts. 🎁Also, There will be a 30 day private TBG Facebook group for all the support you need to stay accountable and motivated! 🎁And of course I’ll be holding weekly group Q&A’s on Facebook Live.

The time to change your life is now.

TBG LIVE: Reset & Rebalance is now open for enrollment! Tag a friend below and let’s RESET those old habits and REBALANCE our lives together. #tbglive

Link in bio!

node.text:
If there’s one thing I want my daughter to know, it’s that life isn’t meant to be lived alone.

Trying new things and making new friends can be intimidating- especially the older we get.

But if we want to make changes in our life, we need to open our heart and then show up for it with action.

Most of these women came into my life 3 years ago through a fitness challenge I ran. We talked about routines, nutrition, but more importantly how to break through fear and the barriers that hold us down.

Last week we met up in LA to see Kygo and shared our stories, over tacos and enchiladas, of how we have transformed ourselves, and how we did it with support in our community.

So the Secret to change, in my experience, is to get around WOMEN WHO SUPPORT OTHER WOMEN.🦋✨

Tag a friend who inspires YOU to be better below! 👯‍♀️ 💕✨🌸

node.text:
If postpartum hair loss wasn't enough, now that Andara is grabbing and holding things, she's pulling my hair out just as fast! 😂😂

I honestly thought I would be an exception to the general rule of postpartum hair loss. I told myself, I eat well, I take my supplements like collagen, etc, but, it didn't matter...those postpartum hormones are no joke, and I've got spots of hair thinning especially around the hairline.
 
🤩 Thankfully I reached out to a few of my friends, and they recommended @nutrafol to add to my regular vitamin and supplement routine! Nutrafol Postpartum is compatible with most postnatals and multivitamins, so it can be taken immediately after birth. The ingredients in the formula are  traditionally used during lactation and is breastfeeding-friendly. I just started taking these and cannot wait to share my results with you all in a few weeks/months. I would love for you guys to join me on this hair growth journey. You can head to my stories and shop the link and you’ll get $50 off your first 3 months of subscription. That makes 3-months of supply setting you up for consistency & ultimately success. I would encourage you guys to try this with me, and we can share our results together. Do you suffer from postpartum hair loss? Share your struggles with me in the comments below and let's empower each other - you are not alone and thanks to @nutrafol there are products out there that can help 
#nutrafolpartner

node.text: 5 months with my little nugget. 😍 The last few weeks have been BIG leaps for us!!! Andara is now touching her toes, picking things up with her hands, and she has upgraded to size 2 diapers!!🥲 I also swear she grew an inch this past week!!! We are working on her rolls from side to side and she can almost sit up on her own!! I think we are gonna try out foods for the first time this week! Any recommendations on first foods AND best spoons/aprons/etc…? It’s a first for both of us!!💕💕 #5monthsold #mybabygirl #mamasgirl

node.text:
Did you know that 70% of our immune system is located in our gut?!!🤯

This means that a HEALTHY gut contributes to a strong immune system, better sleep, improved mood, brain health and more!

We can eat thinks like kefir, sauerkraut, yogurt and other fermented foods… but I prefer a supplement to ensure that my gut is supported every day! ☀️

This is why Probiotics are a STAPLE in my routine.🙌

I take one daily, first thing in the morning, with a big glass of water 💧to help promote a healthy gut. A simple habit that can have a  BIG impact on our Heath, immunity, mood and skin!✨

 Here are a few reasons why probiotics are so important!!
▫️They can help GI issues.💚
▫️They can help to prevent Urinary tract infections!
▫️They strengthen your immune system - which is especially important right now as we head into back to school season!! ✍️
▫️They help restore good bacteria in the body, which can support overall wellbeing.♥️
▫️They support digestion and can help to reduce constipation, gas and bloating - something that too many of us have too often!! 💨 

I use these @gardenoflife women’s daily dr formulated probiotics as part of my daily vitamin and supplement regime! They have seriously helped me so much as my body changes and adapts postpartum.👩‍🍼
They have even helped me with some of my skin issues (which…did you know that skin issues can often be related back to gut issues?!)

Want to learn more?! Ask me anything below and either myself or one of @gardenoflife ‘s expert nutritionists will be able to help!!

And always be sure to consult your doctor before making any changes to your diet.

#learneveryday #golpartner #guthealth

I think I’d have to say… that becoming a mommy is the best thing that has ever happened to me. 🥲

Every day I wake up wanting to be better, more loving, and more focused with my energy to build a spectacular life for you, baby girl.

But most of all, I am learning to be kinder and softer to myself .🙏

#mygirl #motivatedmama

node.text: 4.5 months already?! 🥲 Is she starting to look like her mama? 😍 Or do you still mainly see Miles in her??👶🏼 Honestly I can’t tell who she looks more like- but I love to say she’s the perfect blend of us. How amazing is it that humans get to do that??😍 Also, she reaches out to hold my hand now.🥲🥲 #proudmama

node.text: Happy Sunday!! We are back home and settled from our trip to Tennessee!✈️ It was our second trip with Andara and we are getting smarter and more resilient each time.🙃 She was so sweet on the planes but for some reason hates her car seat now. 😅😅 Not sure if that’s part of the 4 month growth spurt but BOY would we appreciate any tips on how parents have overcome this!! 🙏🚗 👶🏼💕

node.text:
I remember the first time I breastfed in public.

Andara was 3 days old and we went to lunch after her first pediatrician appointment.

I wanted to run into Homegoods next door to buy a few essentials… but Andara started to cry because she needed to eat.

Miles and I began to panic ( as this was our first outing as new parents) and ran through a list of ways we could feed her. We concluded that I could sit in the backseat of the car (where the windows were most tinted)  and feed her for 20-30 mins AND THEN run in, while getting our current food to go.

And then it hit me.

All the stories and captions I’ve read about dropping the stigma that breastfeeding is “inappropriate” or “offensive”.. and how many mommas hide in the closet, bathroom stall, or car, as if doing something to be ashamed about.

And I was unknowingly feeding into that.

But feeding a baby isn’t shameful. It’s important. And whether it’s breast or bottle, it’s hard f*ckin work.

So let’s respect our mommas and support them. A smile and a nod can go a long way.
#breastfeedingawarenessweek #worldbreastfeedingweek
